a_n
\psi(x,t) = \sum_{n=0}^\infty a_ne^{-\kappa\lambda_n^2t}\cos(\lambda_nx),
\lambda_n = (1+2n)\frac{\pi}{2L},
\psi(x,0) = \phi(x),
\phi(x)=\frac{RL^2}{2k}\left[1-\frac{x^2}{L^2}\right].
\sum_{n=0}^\infty a_n\cos(\lambda_nx) = \phi(x).
\int_{-2L}^{2L}\cos(\lambda_nx)\cos(\lambda_kx)dx = \cases{2L, \quad n = k\\0, \quad n \neq k},
a_k2L = \int_{-2L}^{2L}\phi(x)\cos(\lambda_kx)dx
\Rightarrow a_k = -\frac{8 L^2 R}{k\pi^2(1 + 2n)^2}.
